Module Title: Programming


This program is a multiple-choice quiz application developed in Python for. The application
allows a user to select a quiz topic, answer ten questions, receive a final score, and review
both their answers and the correct answers at the end of the quiz.

Four quiz topics:
History
General Knowledge
Coding
Bible

Each topic contains 10 multiple-choice questions and menu-based topic selection
After the quiz it automatically calculates your score

HOW THE PROGRAM WORKS
- The program displays a welcome message and quiz instructions.
- You select one of the four topics.
- Ten questions are displayed one at a time.
- The user enters an answer (A, B, C, or D) for each question.
-If the user enters an invalid input you have to try again.

After all questions are answered:
- The final score is displayed
- Feedback is then given based on the score you got
- A full answer review is shown after the feedback showing the correct answers



